  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  All patients with suspicious or confirmed sepsis at admission or during stay in ICU

          -  Patients with antibiotic duration of less than 48 hours before enrollment

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Age less than or equal to 18 years

          -  Known pregnancy

          -  Specific infections for which long-term antibiotic treatment for 3 weeks more is
             strongly recommended: infective endocarditis, empyema, osteomyelitis et al.

          -  severe immunocompromised patients : HIV infected patients (CD4 count &lt; 200 cells/mm3),
             Neutropenia (ANC count &lt; 500/mm3)

          -  Presence of do-not-resuscitate order
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
    <gender>All</gender>
